<article class="comment" id="comment5751137" data-author="users/94881" data-subject="comments/5751137" data-dislikes="0" data-id="5751137">
<p class="avatar"><a rel="nofollow" title="thedevilsjester" href="/users/thedevilsjester"><img class="framed lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA4MCA4MCI+PC9zdmc+" width="80" height="80" data-original="https://images.pushsquare.com/users/94881/avatar.jpg?v=1393602053" alt="thedevilsjester" /></a></p>
<div class="detail"><ul class="info"><li class=" first"><a class="num" rel="nofollow" href="news/2020/08/next_ps5_announcement_tentatively_scheduled_for_this_month_says_new_report#comment5751137">41</a></li><li><a rel="nofollow" class="username accent" title="thedevilsjester" href="/users/thedevilsjester">thedevilsjester</a></li><li class=" last"><time class="date age " datetime="2020-08-05T18:21:39+00:00"><span>Wed 5th Aug 2020</span></time></li></ul>
<section class="text">
<p>As many have said, I doubt the price will be higher than $499, so just for the sake of planning, assume its $499. If the difference of $50-$100 is make or break for you right now, you should probably not be an early adopter and just wait until you have more disposable income or the price drops to one you are more comfortable with.</p></section>
